'''Eldric the Ice King''' is a [[Giant (race)|giant]] boss, being one of the [[Royal Titans]], along with [[Branda the Fire Queen]]. Like [[Scurrius]] and [[Amoxliatl]], the Royal Titans are considered an entry-level boss designed for players with 70-90+ combat level, and is meant to introduce the practice of gear switching.

Despite his high ranged defence of 700, the player's ranged accuracy is increased by 500% (x6) whenever he is out of melee distance,{{CiteNews|url=https://secure.runescape.com/m=news/game-jam-poh-improvements?oldschool=1|title=Game Jam: POH Improvements|newsdate=26 February 2025|quote=The moment a Royal Titan starts retreating from Melee range, it becomes far more vulnerable to Ranged attacks. While it's in this state, your Ranged Accuracy gets a whopping 500% boost - meaning your hits are going to land much more reliably. This effect lasts until the Titan turns around to re-engage in Melee combat, so keep those arrows flying while you have the advantage! The Accuracy buff also applies during the charge-up pulse attack in Stage 3, covering both the charging phase and the attack itself.}} and lasts until he moves back within melee distance. This boost also applies during the entirety of the Titans' Elemental Blast attack, which includes the charging portion. As such, players are incentivised to attack him with melee when possible.

Eldric uniquely drops the [[deadeye prayer scroll]], which unlocks the [[Deadeye]] prayer - a direct upgrade to the [[Eagle Eye]] prayer. Furthermore, he drops the [[ice element staff crown]], which along with the [[fire element staff crown]] (dropped by [[Branda the Fire Queen]]) and a [[battlestaff]], are combined to create the [[twinflame staff]].

